00:24:13,740 --> 00:24:14,820
(Jin didn't need an alibi)
So we lowered

783
00:24:14,820 --> 00:24:16,100
(Ruling out by motive)
our suspicion of Jin.

784
00:24:16,100 --> 00:24:17,580
Looking at the other three people,

785
00:24:18,700 --> 00:24:19,700
I realized

786
00:24:19,700 --> 00:24:21,180
Ning was special to Ke.

787
00:24:21,180 --> 00:24:22,740
(Sorting through relationships
to find the accomplice)

788
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:25,380
Ning used to be Ke's senior and savior.

789
00:24:25,380 --> 00:24:27,060
If Ning suddenly became a bad guy,

790
00:24:27,060 --> 00:24:28,820
Ke would definitely find it strange.

791
00:24:28,820 --> 00:24:30,020
Something suddenly occurred to me.

792
00:24:30,020 --> 00:24:32,220
(Analyzing their past)
He'd be very curious

793
00:24:32,220 --> 00:24:33,700
(Further narrowing down the killer)
about why Ning suddenly turned bad.

794
00:24:33,700 --> 00:24:35,260
So he was more likely to find proof

795
00:24:35,260 --> 00:24:36,980
that Ning was actually a good guy.

796
00:24:36,980 --> 00:24:39,140
So in the end, I voted for Ke and Ning.

797
